-- UBS Hires Goldman Partner Jasper Tans for Europe ECM Team
-- B y   R u t h   D a v i d   a n d   Z i j i n g   W u
-- 2012-09-27T16:27:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-27/ubs-hires-goldman-partner-jasper-tans-for-europe-ecm-team.html
UBS AG (UBSN) , Switzerlandâ€™s biggest bank,
hired Jasper Tans as a managing director for its equity capital
markets team in London starting Oct. 1, according to an internal
memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  Tans will report to Darrell Uden and Chicco di Stasi, the
co-heads of ECM in Europe, the  Middle East  and Africa. He will
be responsible for Scandinavia, Benelux and financial
institutions clients, as well as providing specialist coverage,
according to the memo.  Companies in Europe, the Middle East and Africa raised $46
billion in equity offerings so far this year, compared with
$82.3 billion in the same period a year ago, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg. Goldman Sachs Group Inc. ranks first
among managers of equity sales in the region while UBS is
seventh, the data show.  Tans became a partner at Goldman in 2010, leading the Japan
financing group, and returned to London last year.  -- Editors: Chris V. Nicholson, Jacqueline Simmons  To contact the reporter on this story:
